24/03/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- US Vice President Dick Cheney arrives in Ankara on Monday (March 24th) as part of his Middle East tour. Talks with President Abdullah Gul, Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan and chief of General Staff, General Yasar Buyukanit are expected to focus on the situation in Iraq and Afghanistan, Iran's nuclear programme, the deployment of missile systems in Europe and prospects for a settlement of the Arab-Israeli conflict. Turkish officials are also expected to bring up efforts to combat the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK), which has been launching attacks against Turkey from bases in northern Iraq.
Turkmenistan's President Gurbanguly Berdymukhamedov is also expected in Ankara Monday, kicking off a two-day trip at Gul's invitation. (RIA-Novosti, CNN Turk - 24/03/08; Anadolu news agency - 23/03/08)
